pgTitle: List of NFL quarterbacks who have passed for 400 or more yards in a game

rows.text: NFL record (set): Most touchdown passes thrown in a game.
2nd career 400-yard game. First quarterback with more than one career 400-yard game. NFL record (tied): Most touchdown passes thrown in a game.
NFL record (tied): Most touchdown passes thrown in a game.
3rd career 400-yard game. Surpassed George Blanda for most career 400-yard games.
Postseason 400-yard #001: 1st QB with 400-yard postseason performance. AFL Championship. Lowest completion perecentage (42.6%).
NFL record (tied): Most touchdown passes thrown in a game.
Postseason 400-yard #002: 2nd QB. AFC Divisional. 2nd career 400-yard game. 1st NFL game & 1st postseason game with two 400-yard QBs (vs. Don Strock).
Postseason 400-yard #003: 3rd QB. AFC Divisional. Did not start game. 1st NFL game & 1st postseason game with two 400-yard QBs (vs. Dan Fouts).
4th career 400-yard game. 2nd NFL game & 1st regular-season game with two 400-yard QBs (vs. Ken Anderson). Fouts' 2nd game where both QBs passed 400-yards.
2nd NFL game & 1st regular-season game with two 400-yard QBs (vs. Dan Fouts). 2nd career 400-yard game.
Postseason 400-yard #004: 4th QB. AFC Championship. 5th career 400-yard game.
6th career 400-yard game. Surpassed Sonny Jurgensen and Dan Marino for most career 400-yard games.
3rd career 400-yard game. 1st QB with consecutive 400-yard games. NFL Record: 945 yards over two consecutive games.
6th career 400-yard game. 3rd NFL game with two 400-yard QBs. First QB in NFL history to throw for 6 TDs and lose the game.
2nd career 400-yard game. NFL record (tied): perfect 158.3 rating.
8th career 400-yard game. Surpassed Dan Fouts for most career 400-yard games.
Postseason 400-yard #005: 5th QB. AFC Divisional. 3rd career 400-yard game. NFL Record: Most yardage in postseason.
3rd career 400-yard game. Lowest QB rating in a 400-yard game.
12th career 400-yard game. 5th NFL game with two 400-yard QBs.
2nd career 400-yard game; also set NFL records for single game passing attempts and completions.
Postseason 400-yard #008: 1st QB with postseason repeat. AFC Wild Card. 15th career 400-yard game, 2nd in postseaon.
Postseason 400-yard #010: 9th QB. Super Bowl. NFL Record: Most yards in Super Bowl
2nd career 400-yard game. Highest completion percentage (81.8%, tie)
2nd career 400-yard game. Fourth QB with consecutive 400-yard games.
Postseason 400-yard #012: 11th QB. AFC Wild Card. NFL Record: Postseason rating. 7th career 400-yard game. Highest completion percentage (81.8%, tie).
Highest QB rating in a losing effort with 400+ yards.
Postseason 400-yard #013: 2nd QB with postseason repeat. AFC Divisional. 9th career 400-yard game, 2nd in postseason.
First QB with 400+ passing yards and 60+ rushing yards in the same game.
2nd career 400-yard game, fifth QB with consecutive 400-yard games.
Youngest QB in terms of age with 400-yard passing game.
Postseason 400-yard #014: 12th QB. NFC Wild Card round.
2nd career 400-yard game. 6th NFL game and 5th regular-season game with two 400-yard QBs.
3rd career 400-yard game. 6th NFL game and 5th regular-season game with two 400-yard QBs.
Postseason 400-yard #015: 13th QB. NFC Wild Card round. 6th career 400-yard game.
Equaled Matthew Stafford's record for most passing yards in a game by a rookie. First career start.
Along with Tom Brady's 517 yards, it is the seventh time in history that two QBs surpass 400 yards in one game.
NFL record: Most passing yards in a game by a rookie. Second 400-yard game and second career start. Sixth QB, and first rookie, with consecutive 400-yard games.
3rd career 400-yard game. Seventh QB with consecutive 400-yard games.
3rd career 400-yard game. 2nd QB ever with three 400-yard passing games in one season.

NFL Record: 1,000 combined yards in game. Along with Matt Flynn's 480 yards, it is the eighth time in history that two QBs surpass 400 yards in one game. 4th career 400-yard game. First game in history that two QBs passed for 400 yards and 5 TDs each.
NFL Record: 1,000 combined yards in game. Eighth game in history that two QBs surpass 400 yards in one game. First game in history that two QBs passed for 400 yards and 5 TDs each.
Postseason 400-yard #016: 1st QB with consecutive 400-yard postseason games. NFC Wild Card Round. 9th career 400-yard game, 2nd in postseason. Most yards in a regulation postseason game.

Postseason 400-yard #017: 1st QB with 3 – and 3 consecutive – 400-yard postseason games. NFC Divisional Round. 10th career 400-yard game, 3rd in postseason. First QB with consecutive 400-yard games in a single postseason.
4th career 400-yard game. Thirteenth NFL quarterback to break 500 yards.
4th Rookie to pass for 400 Yards in a game
NFL record: Most passing yards in a game by a rookie.
4th career 400-yard game, tied for 2nd for passing yards in a game
6th career 400-yard game, new NFL record for most yards (443) in a regular season game with 0 TDs.
4th career 400-yard game. 3rd QB ever with three 400-yard passing games in one season.
NFL record (tied): Most touchdown passes thrown in a game.
Although this was his first career 400-yard passing game, Kaepernick put up a combined 444 yards in SF's last meeting with GB
NFL record (tied): Most touchdown passes thrown in a game. NFL record (tied): perfect 158.3 rating.
